                    <!--Lists the various local mag's in charge at the time that either cleaning, or construction of a colonnade was undertaken, by Diodoros. Cited in discussion of gymnasia evidence by Nenci, 1991, 923; note that Delorme 1960: 288 n.7, 487 rejected the restoration of the word 'xystos', which goes back to 1836, and with that rejection, the link to a gymnasium becomes tenuous to say the least. But generally cited in support of existence of Segestan gymnasium. Nenci 1991, 924 for date, and cf. SEG 41.825.--></p>
